{
  "stem": "25423.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, then the Germans-- the Russians started to bomb the city, night after night.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Subsequently, you could hear the artillery battles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then there was quiet for two, three months, so the Germans running out in the less and less orderly fashion.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One day, carrying books to the residence of the metropolitan, I stumbled on the Russian sniper, a woman, lying there, and I realized that the Russians are in the city.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What does it mean?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Formal?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not only that, but I kept still my Ukrainian identity.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't want to say anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I still acted and waited for three, four weeks until you see the situation stabilize.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Germans could have come back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not at that time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I discussed it with Klyment, who was a very wise man.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he pointed out to me that if I stay in Lwow, I would be mobilized to the Russian army.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as Poland is liberated, and there is a Polish committee of national liberation in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It would be prudent to move there and, contact [INAUDIBLE] because he had the same misconceptions I had, that Jews would take care of these survivors, and they will be, in a way, provided with assistance and so forth, which was not the case.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyway, after about two months, I decided to move on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I crossed the border, or the demarcation line is better, between the newly created Poland and Russia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because the territory where I was was formally annexed to the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Rawa Ruska.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the border line, is after Rawa Ruska.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Still today.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First, to Rawa Ruska.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I crossed the distance of the local Greek Catholic priests.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Until Rawa Ruska, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From Rawa Ruska, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
